DC Board of Elections Sued for Keeping Voter Data Secret | Epoch Times (https://www.theepochtimes.com/d-c-board-of-elections-sued-for-keeping-voter-data-secret_4144019.html)

A good-government group is suing the District of Columbia in federal court for refusing to allow the inspection of voter list maintenance records as required by federal law.

The D.C. Board of Elections claims it can‚Äôt provide the voter list maintenance documents because of its contract with the Electronic Registration Information Center (ERIC), a nonprofit that describes (https://ericstates.org/) its mission as ‚Äúassisting states to improve the accuracy of America‚Äôs voter rolls and increase access to voter registration for all eligible citizens.‚Äù ERIC was created in 2012 with assistance from The Pew Charitable Trusts, a left-wing philanthropy.

The District of Columbia, along with 31 states, outsources the maintenance of its voter rolls to ERIC. ERIC regularly provides the district board with reports showing which registered voters are no longer eligible because they have died or relocated. The National Voter Registration Act of 1993 says that all records used to add or remove voters are public records, yet the board denied a group‚Äôs request to inspect the reports ERIC provides to the board.

According to the Public Interest Legal Foundation (https://twitter.com/pilfoundation?s=21) (PILF), which brought this lawsuit (https://publicinterestlegal.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1-Complaint-DC-ERIC.pdf), ERIC has a history of inaccuracy in removing deceased and other ineligible registrants from voter rolls.

‚ÄúERIC is being used to hide decisions about who gets to vote and who is removed from the rolls,‚Äù said PILF President J. Christian Adams, a former U.S. Justice Department civil rights attorney.

For nearly sixty years, I've been a Cockie

But it's nearly over now, and now I'm easy

But it's nearly over now, and now I'm easy

But it's nearly over now, and now I'm easy

Julian Assange Gives a Warning About ‚ÄòTriangle Of Terror‚Äô ‚Äì Clinton, Pentagon & Google

Julian Assange has warned that Wall Street and multinational corporations are no longer merely exercising power, but are now literally ruling over us, and cautioned that a Clinton White House will feature an unprecedented merger between the private power of corporations and the military might of the state.

Speaking via video feed at the Green Party convention in Houston, Texas, Assange said Google‚Äôs goal is ‚Äúto integrate with Washington, to prevent antitrust regulation and to be part of that family of traditional D.C.-mediated power.‚Äù

The consequences for the 21st century of such a collusion will be similar to the consequences for the 20th century provided by the merging of the state with military-industrial giants like Lockheed Martin, Assange claims.

‚ÄúGoogle has been to the White House, on average over the last four years, once per week‚Äîmore than any other single company. It spends more money lobbying Washington, D.C., than any other single company. The chairman of Google, who was the CEO of Google, Eric Schmidt, has started, about a year ago, a company to run Hillary Clinton‚Äôs digital campaign.

Hillary Clinton‚Äôs former staffer, Jared Cohen, was hired by Google in 2009 to head up Google‚Äôs internal think tank. There‚Äôs a lot of other interconnections between Google and the state. Eric Schmidt is now also, at the same time as being chairman of what is now Google‚Äôs parent company, Alphabet, is chairman of the Pentagon innovation board.

So you have a connection between Google, the Clinton campaign, which will be almost certainly the next White House, and the Pentagon. And this triangle is extremely worrying, because, as time goes by, Google is understanding that it does have an ability to influence election campaigns. It‚Äôs also bought more than 10 drone companies. It‚Äôs integrating its mapping data in order to better be able to fly and navigate drones around the world, is expanding into every country in the world.

And it has a very strange, quasi-religious vision of the future, of this vision of the singularity. I‚Äôve done research that it‚Äôs very disturbing what they believe in Silicon Valley, that they believe they can create a massive artificial intelligence, more powerful than any human being or any society‚Äôs ability to think. And, of course, we all know what happens when such power is in limited hands.

And so, Google in the White House will be, essentially, an unregulatable company. It‚Äôs a question whether it‚Äôs already unregulatable, but you can‚Äîyou can just completely forget about any kind of antitrust legislation being used on Google if there is a Hillary Clinton White House.
